festival.introText:
About Restricted Forest

Restricted Forest delivers what you have been waiting for with a music festival from the genres of House, Techno, Old Skool and more, in a woodland setting of Witton Park, Blackburn Lancashire.
festival.descriptionText: Get more information about Restricted Forest 2023 including festival tickets, news, reviews and lineups.

faqs.question: DoesRestricted Foresthave onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Restricted Forest is a non camping festival so camping equipment is not needed.

faqs.question: Where is Restricted Forest?
faqs.answer: Restricted Forest is located in Witton Country Park. The postcode is BB2 2TP.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: No Payment Plan tickets are not yet available.

faqs.question: DoesRestricted Forest have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Restricted Forest.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Restricted Forest?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Restricted Forest. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival.
